Description: The Temptation of St Antony; he is seated and reads the scriptures accompanied by his attribute the swine with a monkey-like devilish creature and a naked female tempting him; beyond a group of buildings are in flames; copy of a print by Hieronymus Wierix after Maarten de Vos Engraving
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (1080, copy) (Maarten de Vos)
Mauquoy-Hendrickx 1979 / Les Estampes des Wierix ... catalogue raisonné (1065, copy)
Alvin 1866 / Catalogue raisonné de l'oeuvre des trois frères Jan, Jérome et Antoine Wierix (847, copy)
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
